# Frontend Conventions

## Stack

- Vue 3 (Composition API with `<script setup>`)
- Vite, Pinia, Vue Router
- fetch API for HTTP (credentials: 'include' for cookies)
- SSE via fetch + ReadableStream (not EventSource, because POST is needed)

## Structure

- `pages/` — route-level components (LoginPage, ChatPage, AdminPage)
- `components/` — reusable UI components
- `stores/` — Pinia stores (auth, chat, admin)
- `api/` — HTTP client functions grouped by domain
- `router/` — Vue Router with navigation guards

## Patterns

- Use `<script setup>` syntax in all components
- Use Pinia stores for shared state, not props drilling
- API calls live in `api/*.js`, not in components or stores directly
- Handle loading/error states in stores (`isLoading`, `error`)
- Use `credentials: 'include'` on all fetch calls (session cookies)

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase files (`ChatSidebar.vue`)
- Stores/API: camelCase files (`auth.js`, `chat.js`)
- CSS: scoped styles in components, global styles in `assets/styles/`
